The paper discusses the evaluation of an anomaly-based DDoS detection system, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The system uses regression models to estimate the strength of DDoS attacks, which involves network infrastructure (cs.NI) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The paper also mentions the use of statistical performance measures, which falls under the category of statistical learning (cs.SI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
